synopses.synopsis: The weekly stories followed Edmond Dantes, who escaped from an infamous French prison in the early post-Napoleonic era and rose to become one of literature's great crusaders for justice. Originally imprisoned on a false charge of treason, Dantes became established as the count of the island of Monte Cristo, and from this home base he poured reprisals upon the heads of his evil and hated enemies. - On the Air: The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio by John Dunning
